crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The code defines a class called LutBuilder that can build a MorphLut from a descriptive language. The MorphLut is used for binary morphological operations on images. The LutBuilder class has methods to add patterns, build a default lut, get the lut, permute strings and patterns, and build the lut based on the patterns. The code also defines a class called MorphOp that can apply morphological operations on images using a lut. The MorphOp class has methods to apply the operation, get matching coordinates, get all turned on pixels in a binary image, load an operator from an mrl file, save an operator to an mrl file, and set the lut from an external source.
